<item>
            <title>[LU-15990] &quot;lfs find&quot; to scan for directory hash flags</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15990</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It does not currently appear possible to run &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs find&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to locate directories in the filesystem that are only partially migrated (i.e. directories with the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;migrating&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; flag set).  This is useful for two reasons:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;to be able to scan the filesystem to locate directories that have not completed MDT migration (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14719&quot; title=&quot;&amp;quot;lfs migrate -m&amp;quot; creates broken agent inodes when target MDT full&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14719&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14719&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;to be able to restart/finish the MDT migration for those directories (&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14211&quot; title=&quot;DNE3: mechanism to interrupt and resume migration&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14211&quot;&gt;LU-14211&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15001&quot; title=&quot;improve recovery of interrupted directory migrate&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-15001&quot;&gt;LU-15001&lt;/a&gt;), assuming the reason the migration was interrupted has been resolved&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
